Japanese Bought Net 104.9 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 
2011-06-22T23:55:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/japanese-bought-net-104-9-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended June 17 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 104.9 billion yen ($1.3 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 129.1 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 35.1 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 269.1 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 95.7 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 190.5 billion yen in stocks, and bought 1437.8 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 1342.9
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Minh Bui in Tokyo at   mbui@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  